## 🔧 config/database.php

```php
<?php
$conn = mysqli_connect("localhost","root","","aws_voting");
// Connects to MySQL server running on localhost (XAMPP)
// "root" = default XAMPP username, "" = no password
// "aws_voting" = the database name

if(!$conn){ die("Database Connection Failed"); }
// If connection fails, stop the entire page and show error
// die() halts PHP execution immediately
?>
```

---

## 🔐 admin/includes/header.php — Line-by-Line

```php
if(!isset($_SESSION['admin'])){
    header("Location: login.php");
    exit();
}
```
**Why?** This is an **auth guard**. Every admin page includes this file. If there is no `admin` session (user is not logged in), it immediately redirects to `login.php`. The `exit()` is critical — without it, PHP would continue executing the rest of the page even after sending the redirect header.

```php
$admin_name = htmlspecialchars($_SESSION['admin']);
```
**Why?** `htmlspecialchars()` converts special characters like `<`, `>`, `&` into safe HTML entities. This prevents **XSS attacks** — if someone somehow injected `<script>` into the admin name, it would be rendered as harmless text, not executable code.

```php
$current = basename($_SERVER['PHP_SELF']);
```
**Why?** `$_SERVER['PHP_SELF']` returns the full path like `/aws-voting-advanced/admin/dashboard.php`. `basename()` strips the directory path and returns just `dashboard.php`. This is used to detect which page is currently active, so the sidebar can highlight the correct navigation link.

```php
$nav_items = [
    'dashboard.php' => ['icon' => '📊', 'label' => 'Dashboard'],
    // ...
];
```
**Why?** This is a PHP **associative array** that stores all sidebar navigation links. Instead of writing 8 separate `<a>` tags in HTML, we store them in an array and loop through them. This makes it easy to add/remove/reorder navigation items in one place.

```php
<?php foreach($nav_items as $file => $item): ?>
<a href="<?php echo $file; ?>"
   class="sidebar-link <?php echo ($current === $file) ? 'active' : ''; ?>">
```
**Why?** The `foreach` loop generates one link per navigation item. The `($current === $file) ? 'active' : ''` is a **ternary operator** — it checks if the current page filename matches this link's filename. If yes, it adds the CSS class `active` which highlights it in the sidebar.

```php
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```
**Why?** Makes the page **responsive** on mobile devices. Without this, phones would render the page at desktop width and then shrink it, making text tiny and unreadable.

```php
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
```
**Why?** Tells the browser to start connecting to Google's font servers early, **before** it even sees the font stylesheet. This speeds up font loading by ~100-300ms.

```php
<a href="logout.php" class="topbar-logout">🚪 Logout</a>
```
**Why?** The logout button is placed in the topbar (top-right corner) for quick access on every admin page.

