## 🔍 JavaScript Search (used in voters, candidates, feedback pages)

```javascript
document.getElementById("searchBox").addEventListener("keyup", function(){
    const val = this.value.toLowerCase();
    document.querySelectorAll("#voterTable tbody tr").forEach(row => {
        row.style.display = row.innerText.toLowerCase().includes(val) ? "" : "none";
    });
});
```
**Why?**
- `addEventListener("keyup", ...)` — runs the function every time a key is released in the search box
- `this.value.toLowerCase()` — gets the search text, converted to lowercase for case-insensitive matching
- `querySelectorAll("tbody tr")` — selects every row in the table body
- `row.innerText.toLowerCase().includes(val)` — checks if the row's text content contains the search query
- `display = "" vs "none"` — shows or hides the row. Empty string `""` resets to default display (visible)

This is a **client-side search** — it filters rows that are already loaded on the page, so it's instant with no server requests.

