## 🗄️ Database Tables Summary

| Table | Purpose | Key Columns |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `admins` | Admin accounts | `id`, `username`, `password` |
| `users` | Voter accounts | `id`, `name`, `email`, `password`, `has_voted`, `type` |
| `elections` | Election events | `id`, `title`, `type`, `start_date`, `end_date`, `status` |
| `candidates` | Election candidates | `id`, `name`, `position`, `election_id`, `image` |
| `votes` | Cast votes | `id`, `user_id`, `candidate_id`, `election_id` |
| `feedback` | Voter feedback | `id`, `user_id`, `message`, `created_at` |
| `logs` | Admin audit trail | `id`, `action`, `created_at` |

---

## 🛡️ Security Features Summary

| Feature | How It Works |
|---------|-------------|
| **SQL Injection Prevention** | All user input goes through `prepare()` + `bind_param()`, never directly in SQL |
| **XSS Prevention** | All output uses `htmlspecialchars()` to escape HTML |
| **Password Hashing** | New passwords use `password_hash()` (bcrypt) — irreversible |
| **Session Auth Guards** | Every protected page checks `$_SESSION` before showing content |
| **File Upload Safety** | Uploaded files get unique names via `uniqid()` to prevent overwriting |
| **CSRF (partial)** | Forms use POST method; destructive GETs have `confirm()` dialogs |
| **Audit Logging** | All admin actions logged to `logs` table with timestamps |

---

## 📝 Common PHP Functions Used

| Function | What It Does |
|----------|-------------|
| `session_start()` | Starts/resumes a session to store login state |
| `header("Location: ...")` | Sends HTTP redirect to another page |
| `exit()` | Stops PHP execution immediately |
| `htmlspecialchars()` | Escapes HTML to prevent XSS attacks |
| `password_hash()` | Creates a secure one-way hash of a password |
| `password_verify()` | Checks if a password matches its hash |
| `prepare()` + `bind_param()` | Creates safe SQL queries (prevents injection) |
| `fetch_assoc()` | Gets one row as a key-value array |
| `fetch_all(MYSQLI_ASSOC)` | Gets all rows as an array of key-value arrays |
| `date()` | Formats a date/timestamp |
| `trim()` | Removes leading/trailing whitespace |
| `uniqid()` | Generates a unique ID string |
| `basename()` | Extracts filename from a full path |
| `move_uploaded_file()` | Moves an uploaded file to permanent storage |
| `unlink()` | Deletes a file from the server |
